      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/11/12",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ فُضُولِ اَلْكَيْلِ وَ اَلْمَوَازِينِ فَقَالَ \"إِذَا لَمْ يَكُنْ تَعَدَّى فَلاَ بَأْسَ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3783 - It is narrated from Abd Al-Rahman ibn Al-Hajjaj, who said:\nI asked Abu Abdillah (as) about the excess that may result from measuring or weighing.\nImam (as) said: \"If there is no deliberate excess (beyond fairness), then there is no harm.\""
        ]
      }
    },
